                                          FIVERR AND UPWORK REVIEW SUMMARIES
High costs and pay-to-apply system
~50% mentions
Many users criticize the mandatory purchase of "Connects" to apply for jobs, which can be expensive and often wasted on unresponsive or scam job postings. The platform's fees, including a 10% cut on earnings and withdrawal charges, are seen as excessive, creating a financial burden especially for new freelancers struggling to secure their first clients.
Account verification and support issues
~35% mentions
Numerous reviews report difficulties with identity verification processes, including repeated failures to upload IDs or profile pictures, leading to account suspensions without clear explanations. Customer support is frequently described as unhelpful or nearly nonexistent, exacerbating user frustration and trust issues with the platform.
App performance and notification management problems
~25% mentions
Users mention app glitches such as slow performance, bugs, and problematic notification systems that mix important alerts with ads, causing confusion and anxiety. Some report issues with login, password changes, and profile updates, indicating a need for technical improvements to enhance user experience.
**User-Friendly Interface** (approx. 17% mentions) The app has a simple and user-friendly interface that makes it easy for freelancers to send proposals and manage contracts.
**Effective for Career Development** (approx. 10% mentions) Upwork is recognized as a great platform for career development and connecting with international clients.
**Smooth Job Posting Process** (approx. 6% mentions) The process of posting jobs and managing contracts is smooth and efficient for employers.
**Helpful Notifications** (approx. 6% mentions) Real-time notifications for project updates are helpful for users.
**Good for Freelancers** (approx. 5% mentions) Overall, Upwork is considered a good platform for freelancers to earn money through their skills.
**High Cost of Connects** (approx. 20% mentions) The cost of connects is perceived as too high, making it difficult for new freelancers to apply for jobs.
**Account Verification Issues** (approx. 14% mentions) Many users faced problems with account verification, leading to suspensions without clear explanations.
**Technical Difficulties with the App** (approx. 12% mentions) The app frequently experiences technical issues, including login problems and glitches.
**Unfair Proposal System** (approx. 10% mentions) The proposal system is viewed as unfair, with many jobs receiving excessive applications, making it hard to get hired.
**Poor Customer Support** (approx. 9% mentions) Users report frustration with unresponsive customer support and lack of clear communication regarding account issues.
                                     FIVERR
**High Quality and Professional Freelance Work** (approx. 40% mentions) Users consistently praise the platform for connecting them with skilled freelancers who deliver high-quality, professional work on time. Multiple reviews highlight excellent communication, responsiveness, and satisfaction with results across various creative and technical services.
**Ease of Use and Platform Accessibility** (approx. 25% mentions) Many reviewers find the platform and app easy to navigate and use for managing freelance projects, messaging, and payments. The app is appreciated for enabling seamless communication and order tracking, making it a valuable tool for both freelancers and clients.
**Valuable Business and Growth Opportunities** (approx. 20% mentions) Several users emphasize Fiverr's role in helping freelancers and businesses grow by providing access to global talent and diverse services. The platform is recognized as a useful resource for startups and entrepreneurs to outsource tasks efficiently and cost-effectively.
**Prevalence of Scammers and Security Concerns** (approx. 50% mentions) A significant number of reviews report frequent scam and phishing attempts, with many users receiving messages from fraudulent profiles trying to redirect them to external sites. Users express frustration over inadequate platform controls and insufficient protection against scams, leading to distrust and safety concerns.
**Poor Customer Service and Support Accessibility** (approx. 40% mentions) Users frequently complain about unresponsive or ineffective customer service, including difficulty reaching live support and reliance on automated AI responses. Issues such as account suspensions, refund disputes, and verification problems often remain unresolved, causing dissatisfaction and loss of trust.
**High Fees and Complex Pricing Structure** (approx. 30% mentions) Many reviewers criticize the platform's high service fees, including charges on tips, which significantly increase costs for both buyers and sellers. The pricing and order management systems are described as overly complex and non-intuitive, complicating workflow and reducing overall satisfaction.
**App Functionality and Notification Issues** (approx. 25% mentions) Several users report technical problems with the mobile app, including notification failures, bugs in messaging and file uploads, and limited functionality compared to the desktop site. These issues hinder timely communication and project management, impacting user experience negatively.
